title: AP PHOTOS: Memorable Ferraris of the past
text: > Top News AP PHOTOS: Memorable Ferraris of the past FILE - In this Saturday August 10 1996 file photo, Germany's Michael Schumacher drives his Ferrari to set the best time and take pole position for the Hungarian Grand Prix in Budapest. Schumacher's arrival at Ferrari in 1996 marked a turning point for the team, though it would take another four years before he added to his previous two world titles and ended Ferrari's 21-year title drought. He is the most successful driver of all time having won the world title on seven occasions, five with Ferrari. Ferrari's symbol on the New York Stock Exchange says it all - RACE. (AP Photo/Dusan Vranic, File)
